// These have to be manually included within the template because
// we're using Angular to load our views and not inherenting them directly
// with Jade
include /config/variables
include /mixins/mixins

.button.util.padding-10.margin-top-20.margin-bottom-20.block-center(data-ng-class="{true:'background-color-clarity',false:'background-color-dark-grey'}[show_demos]",data-ng-click="show_demos=!show_demos")

	.button__title
		| {{!show_demos&&'Show demos'||'Hide demos'}}

//-@.button

.demos(data-ng-if="show_demos==true")

	:markdown
		This is a list generated by a Jade mixin. It pulls in a Jade object stored in a variable
		and cycles through to generate the list. To see the source, go to /views/mixins/list

	.application-navigation

		mixin list("application-navigation-list","application-navigation-list__enclosure column--large-33","application-navigation-list__item",navigation)

	//-@.navigation

	hr.util.background-color-clarity.margin-top-20

	:markdown
		This data is being pulled from [Reqres](http://reqr.es/) - a fake data API. We're using
		Angular to get and display the data, and then Angular methods to show and hide the appropriate
		previous and next buttons and to incrememnt and re-request the data from the API. To see the source
		go to /views/templates/home and /scripts/application/controllers/user.

		You'll also notice we're taking advantage of many helper classes since we're just prototyping. Many
		of these exist (see stylesheets/utilities). Any configuration of, say, the number of columns generated
		or the amount of padding and margining set up in padding/margin helpers is configured in stylesheets/config/utilities

	.users.util.background-color-clarity.padding-10.margin-bottom-20.margin-top-20(data-ng-controller="UserController")

		ul.list--vertical(data-ng-repeat="user in users.list.data")

			li.list--vertical__enclosure
				{{user.id}}
				{{user.first_name}}
				{{user.last_name}}

		hr.util.margin-top-20.margin-bottom-20

		.button.util.float-left(data-ng-click="users.pages.current=users.pages.current-1;getUsers()",data-ng-if="users.pages.current>1")

			.button__title
				| Previous page

		//-@.button

		.button.util.float-right(data-ng-click="users.pages.current=users.pages.current+1;getUsers()",data-ng-if="users.pages.current<users.pages.total")

			.button__title
				| Next page

		//-@.button

	//-@.users
